verbose_text: These signaling cascades enable the expression of genes that typify the osteoclast lineage including Acp5 (encoding tartrate resistant acid phosphatase [TRAcP]), Ctsk (encoding cathepsin K), and Mmp9 (encoding matrix metalloproteinase 9), thus eventually leading to the formation of mature osteoclasts XREF_BIBR.
